      manual_btn_print:'Print / PDF', manual_close:'Close',
      tour1_title:'1 · The work areas', tour1_text:'This bar switches between the views: <b>Analytics Dashboard</b> (the project numbers at a glance), <b>Case Management</b> (daily work on a single candidate), <b>Matching</b> (hospital requests crossed with the profiles), <b>Documents</b> (the archive with preview of every file) and, for administrators only, <b>Settings</b> (agencies, facilities, operators with their teams, document types and the specialisation catalogue).',
      tour2_title:'2 · Key indicators', tour2_text:'The KPIs summarise the operational status: active cases across the 9 phases, candidates with documents to upload, profiles in the <b>Matching</b> phase, expiring documents and completed paths. <b>Every tile is clickable</b> and opens the pre-filtered list; the three top tiles split candidates between the Dominican Republic Team (to transfer) and the Italy Team (transferred).',
      tour3_title:'3 · Risk alerts', tour3_text:'Each phase has a maximum expected time (SLA): cases stuck beyond it appear here with the days of delay, and below you find documents expired or expiring within 60 days (passports and cédulas included). Click a row to open the case at once: logging an action resets the counter.',
      tour4_title:'4 · Candidate list', tour4_text:'Search by name, passport or facility and filter by status: Transferred/To transfer (the two teams), at risk, missing documents, completed. If your operator profile has a team assigned you also get the <b>"My team"</b> filter, showing only the candidates in your phases. Each card shows the status badge, language level and current phase.',
      tour5_title:'5 · 9-phase path', tour5_text:'The timeline shows the whole path, split between the <b>Dominican Republic Team</b> (phases 1–4) and the <b>Italy Team</b> (phases 5–9). <span class="text-emerald-600 font-semibold">Green</span> = completed, <span class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold">indigo</span> = current phase, <span class="text-amber-600 font-semibold">amber</span> = blocked. Phase <b>7 · Matching</b> is so central that it has a dedicated view: we see it in the next step.',
      tour6_title:'7 · Advance phase', tour6_text:'Back to the candidate’s case. The button unlocks only when the current phase\u2019s checklist and document checks are satisfied: otherwise the missing requirements are listed here. In addition, if the phase belongs to the other team, advancing is reserved to that team: you can see everything but not act (a blue notice tells you).',
      tour7_title:'8 · Document management', tour7_text:'The document lifecycle lives here: <b>Upload</b> the file (PDF or photo, compressed automatically), then <b>Approve</b> or <b>Reject</b>; the status can also be changed from the coloured menu. Documents with a validity date are monitored for expiry, the eye opens the preview and every action is logged. In phase 2 you cannot advance until every required document is uploaded and approved.',
      tour8_title:'9 · Mandatory checklist', tour8_text:'The tasks change with each phase and must all be ticked before advancing: they are the operational translation of the protocol (e.g. in phase 2 sworn translations, apostille, recognition, visa and OPI). The division of labour applies here too: phases 1–4 are ticked by the Dominican Republic Team, phases 5–9 by the Italy Team.',
      tour9_title:'10 · Log & audit trail', tour9_text:'The complete case history: notes, calls and alerts you record, plus every automatic system action (documents approved, phases advanced, matching assignments). It is the traceability that keeps the two teams coordinated: use the form to log a new communication directly in the case.',
      tour10_title:'6 · Demand–supply matching', tour10_text:'This is the view dedicated to phase 7. Here the Italy Team records the <b>facility requests</b> (ward, number of nurses, minimum skills, preferred ones and shift) and with <b>"Find candidates"</b> queries the database: the shortlist is ranked by compatibility, <b>"Eligible profile"</b> means it holds all the minimum skills, and the badges verify documents and the «Italia in tasca» dossier. <b>"Match"</b> updates the candidate\u2019s employer and log; the request stays open until every position is covered.',
      status_missing:'Missing Documents', status_progress:'In Progress', status_visa:'Italy Phase', status_onboarding:'Path Completed',
      tour_back:'Back', tour_next:'Next', tour_finish:'Finish',
